# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat     — new feature or phase             → bumps minor version
#   fix      — bug fix                          → bumps patch version
#   perf     — performance improvement          → bumps patch version
#   revert   — undo a previous commit           → bumps patch version
#   docs     — docs/README/CONTRIBUTING only    → no release
#   chore    — CI, build, deps, tooling         → no release
#   refactor — restructure, no behaviour change → no release
#
# Scopes (optional, use what fits):
#   phase1  phase2  phase3  ssh  ufw  fail2ban  docker  caprover
#   sysctl  lynis   backup  ci   installer      readme
#
# Examples:
#   feat(ssh): add FIDO2 hardware key support
#   fix(sysctl): prevent duplicate entries on re-run
#   fix(phase3): validate SSH public key format before applying
#   chore(ci): add shellcheck workflow
#   docs: add troubleshooting section to README
#   feat!: rename --port flag to --ssh-port  ← ! means breaking change
#
# Rules:
#   - Keep subject line under 72 chars
#   - Use imperative mood: "add" not "added", "fix" not "fixes"
#   - No capital letter after the colon
#   - No full stop at the end
#   - Reference issues in footer: Closes #42
#
